  <h2 id="what-is-an-eml-file">What Is an EML File?</h2>
  <p>
    An EML file is a standard email message saved in the <strong>MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions)</strong> format. Each .eml file represents a single email, including its headers (sender, recipient, subject, date), the message body in plain text or HTML, and any file attachments encoded within the message. The format was originally popularized by Microsoft Outlook Express, but it has since become a widely recognized standard supported by many email clients and archival systems.
  </p>

