  <h3>2. Mozilla Thunderbird</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Thunderbird</strong> is a free, open-source email client developed by Mozilla. It natively supports opening EML files. To view an EML file in Thunderbird, you can simply drag the .eml file into the Thunderbird window, or use <em>File > Open Saved Message</em> from the menu. Thunderbird will display the full email with formatting, inline images, and attachments, just as it would appear in your inbox.
  </p>
  <p>
